## ğŸ“„ README.md - The 30-Second Hook

### Purpose

Hook the reader in under 30 seconds. Answer: What? Why? How to start?

### Template

```markdown
# Project Name

One-liner description < 15 words.

**Problem:** What problem does this solve?
**Solution:** How does it solve it?

## Quick Start

```bash
npm install project-name
project-name init
```

## Status

[![Status](https://img.shields.io/badge/status-stable-success)](https://github.com/user/repo)
[![Version](https://img.shields.io/npm/v/project-name)](https://www.npmjs.com/package/project-name)

## Key Features

- âœ… Feature 1 - Brief description
- âœ… Feature 2 - Brief description
- âœ… Feature 3 - Brief description

## Documentation

- [Getting Started Guide](./GUIDE.md) - 5 minute read
- [API Reference](./REFERENCE.md) - Cheat sheet
- [Contributing](./CONTRIBUTING.md) - For contributors

## License

MIT
```

### README Rules

| âŒ DON'T | âœ… DO |
|----------|--------|
| > 50 lines | Keep under 50 lines |
| "Coming soon" sections | Ship what exists or don't mention |
| Vague descriptions | Specific, actionable |
| Buried lead | Start with Why |
| Multiple install methods | One recommended way |

